Organisation of Report
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The rest of the report is organised and structured as follows:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description

\series bold
Chapter 2
\series default
 presents a comprehensive literature review that underpins the development of the proposed framework.
 It begins by contextualising the current state of multi-robot disaster robotics and highlights the capabilities and limitations of existing heterogeneous SAR systems.
 The discussion then moves into risk assessment methodologies,
 detailing both traversability-based and efficiency-based risks and how these are quantified using frameworks such as Lambda fields.
 Subsequent sections cover localisation and 3D map integration,
 where octree-based and point-cloud approaches are compared for their suitability in real-time fleet coordination.
 The chapter continues with an analysis of risk-aware path planning,
 addressing both physical and energy-based constraints,
 before evaluating communication protocols and coordination models for scalable,
 resilient fleet behaviour in dynamic environments.
 Finally,
 the review explores task allocation strategies,
 particularly those that integrate spatial risk models for intelligent decision-making,
 and evaluates robotic simulation platforms for prototyping and validating heterogeneous fleet deployments.
\end_layout

